Kanuka-Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lynn_Kanuka-Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TEAM USA:Full list of athletes on Olympic team across all sports  The roster's average age is 26.8 years old, which is four years younger than the Tokyo Olympic team.\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.619017900741629, \"rank\": 0.3870271934989221, \"text\": \"TEAM USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9561716310840939, \"rank\": 0.045835512758020426, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One of the biggest things for me ever since I got the job was I want to provide opportunities for less-experienced players,\\\" said Hayes, who was named head coach in November and took over the job in May after her club season leading Chelsea.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C._Women\", \"score\": 0.9999943316444513, \"rank\": 5.668387605367813e-06, \"text\": \"Chelsea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C._Women\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C._Women\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was such a big gap between the top experience and the rest and that we really have to bring that up.\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The volume of players that have not played more than 30 caps was really, really noticeable for me.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So the last eight months has been about giving experiences to bridge that gap.\\\"\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. won four of the first five Olympic women's soccer titles from 1996 through 2012.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans lost in the quarterfinals in Rio in 2016 and took bronze in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1378, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.686874599999519e-20, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.4037539245617505e-12, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1452, \"end\": 1457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9561716310840939, \"rank\": 0.045835512758020426, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. then lost in the round of 16 at last summer's World Cup after winning the previous two World Cups.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Combining the Tokyo Olympics and the 2023 World Cup, the team went back-to-back major tournaments without reaching the final for the first time.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no denying the history of this program has been hugely successful, but the reality is it's going to take a lot of work for us to get to that top level again,\\\" Hayes said.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team is led by Horan, who has been the primary captain for the last year, and Girma, who played every minute of the 2023 World Cup.\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999686224, \"rank\": 2.386025286416714e-11, \"text\": \"Horan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dunn also started all four World Cup matches and has the versatility to play in the attack or defense.\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Naeher, 36, is in line to become the oldest U.S. goalkeeper to play at an Olympics.\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hope Solo was 35 in 2016.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Naeher starred in the Tokyo Olympic quarterfinal win over the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2286, \"end\": 2291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9561716310840939, \"rank\": 0.045835512758020426, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.042551471037281e-11, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She saved an 81st-minute penalty in a 2-2 match, then saved two of the four Dutch shots in a shootout.\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2415, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.7734103166457972, \"rank\": 0.2928708461783925, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With forward Alex Morgan not making the cut, the roster includes zero players from the last Olympic champion team in 2012.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Morgan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.526816134026907e-67, \"text\": \"Alex Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Morgan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Morgan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carli Lloyd and Megan Rapinoe were among the stalwarts who retired since the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2566, \"end\": 2577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carli_Lloyd\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.065044893420635e-67, \"text\": \"Carli Lloyd\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carli_Lloyd\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carli_Lloyd\"}, {\"begin\": 2582, \"end\": 2595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Rapinoe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Megan Rapinoe\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Rapinoe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Rapinoe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic roster is 18 players compared to 23 for the World Cup.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"First off, I want to talk about what an amazing player and human Alex Morgan has been,\\\" Hayes said.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2791, \"end\": 2802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Morgan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.526816134026907e-67, \"text\": \"Alex Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Morgan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Morgan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have only had one opportunity to work with her in the last camp.\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I saw firsthand not just her qualities, but her professionalism.\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her record speaks for itself.\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Second of all, it's not easy making a decision that is only 16 outfield players and two goalkeepers on a roster of 18.\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it was a tough decision, of course, especially considering Alex's history and record with this team, but I felt that I wanted to go in another direction and selected other players.\\\"\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3172, \"end\": 3176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999975116225, \"rank\": 2.487555695910409e-09, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. opens the Paris Olympic tournament against Zambia in Nice on July 25, one day before the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._Open_(golf)\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"U.S. opens\", \"types\": [\